.Dd May 28, 2026
.Dt XTC_APP 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm xtc_app_create ,
.Nm xtc_app_destroy ,
.Nm xtc_app_start ,
.Nm xtc_app_run ,
.Nm xtc_app_stop ,
.Nm xtc_app_loop ,
.Nm xtc_app_registry
.Nd OTP-style application container
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In xtc.h
.In xtc_app.h
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_app_create "const xtc_app_opts_t *opts" "xtc_app_t **out"
.Ft void
.Fn xtc_app_destroy "xtc_app_t *app"
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_app_start "xtc_app_t *app" "const xtc_child_spec_t *children" "int n_children"
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_app_run "xtc_app_t *app"
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_app_stop "xtc_app_t *app"
.Ft "xtc_loop_t *"
.Fn xtc_app_loop "const xtc_app_t *app"
.Ft "xtc_reg_t *"
.Fn xtc_app_registry "const xtc_app_t *app"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm xtc_app
is the L4 application container -- a root supervisor plus a
process registry plus lifecycle plumbing.  Models OTP's
.Sq application
concept.
.Pp
An app owns:
.Bl -bullet -compact -offset indent
.It
A loop
.Pq created if not supplied .
.It
A root supervisor with the configured children.
.It
A process registry where children can find each other by name
.Pq see Xr xtc_reg 3 .
.El
.Pp
Typical usage:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
xtc_app_opts_t opts = XTC_APP_OPTS_DEFAULT;
opts.name = "my_service";
opts.sup.strategy = XTC_SUP_ONE_FOR_ONE;

xtc_app_t *app;
xtc_app_create(&opts, &app);

xtc_child_spec_t kids[] = {
    { .name = "listener",  .fn = listener_proc, .arg = NULL,
      .policy = XTC_RESTART_PERMANENT },
    { .name = "metrics",   .fn = metrics_proc,  .arg = NULL,
      .policy = XTC_RESTART_TRANSIENT },
};
xtc_app_start(app, kids, 2);
xtc_app_run(app);              /* blocks until app stops */
xtc_app_destroy(app);
.Ed
.Pp
The current implementation is single-loop; multi-loop apps spawn
.Xr xtc_exec 3
directly.  Future revisions may grow N-loop apps for thread-per-
core scaling.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr xtc_supervisor 3 ,
.Xr xtc_reg 3 ,
.Xr xtc_loop 3 ,
.Xr xtc 7
.Sh HISTORY
Appeared in xtc 0.1.
